From the manufacturer

Learning fun you can count on

Tiny bankers will love dropping their coins in, taking them out, and pressing the little piggys snout to hear fun songs and sounds that introduce numbers, Spanish words, and more.

Exciting put-and-take play

This toy piggy bank comes with 10 colorful coins for little ones to drop and save in the bank. Open the side door to empty the coins and start the fun all over again!


This toy helps teach & develop:

Numbers & Counting Colors Spanish Words Hand-Eye Coordination Cause & Effect

Switch up the learning as they grow

Level 1 Explore (6M+): Fun phrases and sounds spark your babys curiosity as they drop coins through the slot, open the put-and-take door, or press on piggys nose. Level 2 Encourage (12M+): This level expands on your toddlers learning with fun questions, engaging prompts, and bilingual counting fun in English and Spanish!

What's in the box

  • 1 piggy bank, 10 coins

    How customer reviews and ratings work

    Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

    To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we dont use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzed reviews to verify trustworthiness.

    Sherry W.
    5.0 out of 5 stars 1 year old son on loves it!
    Reviewed in the United States on October 11, 2023
    Style: Piggy BankProduct Packaging: Frustration-Free PackagingVerified Purchase
    We can spend a lot of time together playing with this toy! It's helping him learn how to place the coin into the slot which takes some coordination.
    He also loves opening the latch to get the coins out.
    He also does love tossing the coins around so expect some frequent clean up if your baby is in the throwing everything stage.
    The pig is cute and sings some songs if you press the snout. The pig also counts in English and Spanish depending on the level you choose as baby puts the coins in which will make this useful once he's learning to count.
    The sound quality is great. I think it seems sturdy. I think it could handle some tossing around although I'm lucky he has only thrown the coins and not the pig yet.
    Overall, just a really good and inexpensive toy. Highly recommend!
